NM-CONNECTION-EDITOR(1)                    General Commands Manual                    NM-CONNECTION-EDITOR(1)



NNAAMMEE
       nm-connection-editor - network connection editor for NetworkManager

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       nnmm--ccoonnnneeccttiioonn--eeddiittoorr  [ _O_P_T_I_O_N_S ]


DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       nnmm--ccoonnnneeccttiioonn--eeddiittoorr  is a GTK‐based application to add, remove, and modify network connections stored
       by NetworkManager.  NetworkManager must be running for any network connections to be  added,  removed,
       or modified.


OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --tt,, ----ttyyppee==<<ttyyppee>>
              Type  of connection to create or show.  Values are NetworkManager setting names, eg "802-3-eth‐
              ernet", "802-11-wireless", "bridge", "bond", "wimax", "infiniband", "vlan", etc.  Does  nothing
              if --create or --show is not given.

       --ss,, ----sshhooww
              Expand or collapse the network list to highlight the network connection type given by --type.

       --cc,, ----ccrreeaattee
              Create  a  new  connection  of the type given by --type and allow the user to modify connection
              details.

       --ee,, ----eeddiitt==<<uuuuiidd>>
              Show the network connection edit window for the connection of the given UUID.


SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       nnmmccllii((11)),, NNeettwwoorrkkMMaannaaggeerr((88)),, nnmm--aapppplleett((11))..



                                               15 February 2013                       NM-CONNECTION-EDITOR(1)
